-- U.S. Drought Seen Hindering Energy Independence on Ethanol Stall
-- B y   I s a a c   A r n s d o r f
-- 2012-11-26T09:55:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-26/u-s-drought-seen-hindering-energy-independence-on-ethanol-stall.html
The worst U.S. drought in five
decades is cutting profits from producing corn-based ethanol for
blending in gasoline, hindering the country’s efforts to reach
energy independence, according to Poten & Partners Inc.  Stalling domestic ethanol output led to increased imports,
reversing the nation’s role as a net exporter of the biofuel,
the New York-based shipbroker said in an e-mailed report Nov.
23. That’s boosting demand for tankers as  Brazil  supplies
cargoes to the U.S. East Coast, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Arnsdorf in London at 
